text:
College of the City of New York: Shown is the Lewisohn Stadium as seen from Convent Avenue, near West 136th Street, during repair operations conducted by the Works Progress Administration. In the right background across the amphitheatre is Townsend Harris Hall, and on the left is the tower of the Hebrew Orphan Asylum on the west side of Amsterdam Avenue.

View 2 is at the north end of the Stadium showing the ramp built by the W.P.A. Across same, on the north side of West 138th Street, is the Hygiene Building.

View 3 shows the south ramp of the Stadium under construction. The buildings face on the south side of West 136th Street.

W. P. A. Photo
Five Boroughs Project

January 17, 1937.
Views: 1-2-3
title: Colleges and Universities - College of the City of New York - [City University of New York.]
